4253162;Text mining with R;FALSE;2024-10-25T08:00:00Z;2024-10-25T10:00:00Z;"

Text mining is a powerful set of methods that enable us to process
column2: analyze and visualize the content of a large number of texts. It gives us the possiblity to gain insights and spot patterns that can otherwise be hard to see when reading through the texts. The methods that you will learn on this course can be used to analyze any set of texts.

column1: The advantage of R is that we have a lot of flexibility for our analysis and how we visualize our results. On this course you will learn how to prepare texts for analysis
column2: and how to peform the analysis and visualize the results. Out texts will be summaries from debates in the Danish Parliament Folketinget.

column1: We assume that you have some experience working with R
column2: and knows the tidyverse. The level required is what you would learn on one of our introductory course in "R for absolute beginners".

column1: You should have R and Rstudio installed before the course
column2: and preferably also have downloaded the dataset that we are going to explore. You can find further instructions here.

column1: The course is by default held in English
column2: unless everyone speaks Danish
column3:
in which case it will be in Danish

4202468;R for Absolute Beginners - ONLINE;FALSE;2024-10-29T08:00:00Z;2024-10-29T10:00:00Z;"

R is a general programming language
column2: especially suited for statistical analysis and cleaning and visualization of data.

column1: We assume absolutely no previous experience with programming
column2: and will cover the basics of getting started with R

column1: <ul>
<li>Navigating in RStudio
column2: and how to interact with R

column1: <li>Datatypes
column2: variables and objects

column1: • Simple arithmetic and logical operations on data
• Working with functions - and how to write a very simple function ourself
• Import data into R
• Summary statistics
• Manipulating data frames
<li>And how to make a couple of the common graphs
column2: that are as useful as they are elementary.

column1: In preparation for the course
column2: we recommend that you either download and install R and RStudio
column3: or register for an account at rstudio.cloud. Instructions on this can be found here
column4: where you will also find the course notes
column5: additional material and exercises.

column1:
Please note that this course will be held in english if any participants requests it. Otherwise it will be held in danish.

4216263;NVivo for Absolute Beginners;FALSE;2024-10-29T09:00:00Z;2024-10-29T11:30:00Z;"
Introduction to NVivo; a program which is a great help when you are working with qualitative data analysis.
NVivo can be useful
column2: if you want to organise and/or code your empirical material or literature. It can also be helpful when you want to transcribe audio- or video files

column1: The PC version of NVivo has more functionality than the Mac version
column2: but you can participate in all exercises with either and we will demonstrate in both.

column1: Prior to the course
column2: you must install the version of NVivo called NVivo 14.

column1: This can be done here for Windows:
https://download.qsrinternational.com/Software/NVivo14/NVivo.x64.exe
And here for Mac:
https://download.qsrinternational.com/Software/NVivo14forMac/NVivo.dmg
Registration key is available through the UCPH Software Library.
Please note: NVivo can be found int the Software Library under the link "QSR International - NVivo".
We also recommend that you complete a set of introductory exercises before course start
column2: that you can read about HERE.

column1: 4216240;Python for Absolute Beginners pt. 1;FALSE;2024-10-30T11:00:00Z;2024-10-30T14:00:00Z;"
Note: This is part 1 of 2. You can find part 2 in our course calendar:
https://kubkalender.kb.dk/calendar/datalab
This course is intended for students who have never tried programming before and want to build their skills in Python from the bottom up.
Intimidated by mathematics
column2: numbers
column3: and obscure Python scripts? Don’t be! We will be covering all the very basic concepts and building blocks in order to get complete beginners
column4: who have no experience writing code
column5: working in Python.

column1: This will include explaining the concepts of variables and data types
column2: as well generating some basic scripts to interact with these data
column5: and conditionals. By the end of this course
column6: you will have an understanding of the basic building blocks in Python. You will also come away with an appreciation for how a computer program “thinks”. All we require from you is a will to learn. We look forward to seeing you!

column1: The course is divided in two parts. The first covers different datatypes in Python and how data is stored. In other words
column2: it is an introduction to the building blocks of coding in Python.

column1: The second part expands on this by putting these blocks together to create simple scripts. If you already have some understanding of Python
column2: feel free to skip the first section. Otherwise
column3: we recommend that you start with pt. 1 and then move on to pt. 2.

column1: Practical information: We will be working in Jupyter Lab / Jupyter Notebook
column2: which requires some installation
column3: but you can also work in either Google Colabs or ERDA which require only a Google or KU account
column4: respectively. For more information and help
column5: consult "Install & Run Python" on the course page:

column1: https://kubdatalab.github.io/python
As written
column2: this course is an introduction to the basics of Python. If you have never programmed before
column3: this is a good place to start before you move on to some of our more advanced courses:

column1:
4227301;Orange - Data Mining for Absolute Beginners;FALSE;2024-11-11T08:30:00Z;2024-11-11T10:30:00Z;"

We know that programming can be a barrier for many who are fascinated by text and data mining. Therefore
column2: we are hosting a course on the program Orange.

column1: Orange is a user-friendly software for text and data mining
column2: and the great thing about Orange is that you can use it without needing to know how to program. We call this type of program ‘no-code’ software.

column1: The course is recommended if you want to understand how data
column2: such as digital texts and images
column3: can be transformed and analysed by a computer. In this way the course is relevant for both students and researchers who will be using or assessing digital methods and results.

column1: Orange can handles many of the same tasks and processes that are integrated parts of the concepts of data science that typically is applied to different fields of studies within both natural
column2: social and humanistic science.

column1: On the course you can learn:
<ul role=""list"">
<li 335552541="""" aria-setsize=""-1"" data-aria-level=""1"" data-aria-posinset=""1"" data-font=""Symbol"" data-leveltext="""" data-list-defn-props=""{"">
Data collection of news articles
<li 335552541="""" aria-setsize=""-1"" data-aria-level=""1"" data-aria-posinset=""3"" data-font=""Symbol"" data-leveltext="""" data-list-defn-props=""{"">
Preprocessing before analysis
<li 335552541="""" aria-setsize=""-1"" data-aria-level=""1"" data-aria-posinset=""2"" data-font=""Symbol"" data-leveltext="""" data-list-defn-props=""{"">
Analysis and categorization - both texts and images
<li 335552541="""" aria-setsize=""-1"" data-aria-level=""1"" data-aria-posinset=""2"" data-font=""Symbol"" data-leveltext="""" data-list-defn-props=""{"">
Visualisation
The workshop is based on dialog and switches between short talks and practical solving of small tasks.
Before the course

column1:
4227301;Orange - Data Mining for Absolute Beginners;FALSE;2024-11-11T08:30:00Z;2024-11-11T10:30:00Z;"

We know that programming can be a barrier for many who are fascinated by text and data mining. Therefore
column2: we are hosting a course on the program Orange.

column1: Orange is a user-friendly software for text and data mining
column2: and the great thing about Orange is that you can use it without needing to know how to program. We call this type of program ‘no-code’ software.

column1: The course is recommended if you want to understand how data
column2: such as digital texts and images
column3: can be transformed and analysed by a computer. In this way the course is relevant for both students and researchers who will be using or assessing digital methods and results.

column1: Orange can handles many of the same tasks and processes that are integrated parts of the concepts of data science that typically is applied to different fields of studies within both natural
column2: social and humanistic science.

column1: On the course you can learn:
<ul role=""list"">
<li 335552541="""" aria-setsize=""-1"" data-aria-level=""1"" data-aria-posinset=""1"" data-font=""Symbol"" data-leveltext="""" data-list-defn-props=""{"">
Data collection of news articles
<li 335552541="""" aria-setsize=""-1"" data-aria-level=""1"" data-aria-posinset=""3"" data-font=""Symbol"" data-leveltext="""" data-list-defn-props=""{"">
Preprocessing before analysis
<li 335552541="""" aria-setsize=""-1"" data-aria-level=""1"" data-aria-posinset=""2"" data-font=""Symbol"" data-leveltext="""" data-list-defn-props=""{"">
Analysis and categorization - both texts and images
<li 335552541="""" aria-setsize=""-1"" data-aria-level=""1"" data-aria-posinset=""2"" data-font=""Symbol"" data-leveltext="""" data-list-defn-props=""{"">
Visualisation
The workshop is based on dialog and switches between short talks and practical solving of small tasks.

4251291;R and APIs - Statistics Denmark;FALSE;2024-11-18T09:00:00Z;2024-11-18T11:00:00Z;"

APIs provide access to a multitude of information.
In this course we cover how to extract data though APIs using the Statistics Denmark and i can haz dad joke APIs as examples.
The course material can be found on this website. Please make sure that you have followed the under "Setup" to install R and RStudio as well as some additional packages.
The course requires some previous knowledge of R. We will assume that you are familiar with:
<ul>
<li>Navigating in RStudio
column2: and how to interact with R

column1: <li>Datatypes
column2: variables and objects

column1: • Simple arithmetic and logical operations on data
• Working with functions - and how to write a very simple function ourself
• Import data into R
• Summary statistics
• Manipulating data frames

These topics are covered in our introductory courses in R.

column1: 4216277;NVivo - Cases and Classification in Interview Data;FALSE;2024-11-26T09:00:00Z;2024-11-26T11:30:00Z;"
This course is not an introductory course but presupposes a basic understanding of the functionality in NVivo.
This understanding can be gained by participating in our introductory NVivo courses found here:
https://kubkalender.kb.dk/datalab
In this course
column2: we will expand upon the skills gained in our introductory course (https://absalon.ku.dk/courses/71442/)
column3: and we will be applying cases and case classification to qualitative data.

column1: We will base the course examples on interview data
column2: but both cases and case classifications can be applied to many other types of data.

column1: The PC version of NVivo has more functionality than the Mac version
column2: but you can participate in all exercises with either and we will demonstrate in both.

column1: Prior to the course
column2: you must install the version of NVivo called NVivo 14.

column1: This can be done here for Windows:
https://download.qsrinternational.com/Software/NVivo14/NVivo.x64.exe
And here for Mac:
https://download.qsrinternational.com/Software/NVivo14forMac/NVivo.dmg
Registration key is available through the UCPH Software Library.
Please note: NVivo can be found int the Software Library under the link "QSR International - NVivo".
";https://kubkalender.kb.dk/event/4216277;https://kubkalender.kb.dk/aevent.php?c=6416&m=edit&event_id=4216277;15906;0;KUB Datalab - Samf;40;KUB City Campus
column2: Gothersgade 140

column1: 4293305;Python and Pandas - Getting Started with Data Analysis;FALSE;2024-11-27T11:00:00Z;2024-11-27T14:00:00Z;"
<strong>This course is aimed at students who are new to Pandas but already have an introductory understanding of Python
column2: such as can be gained from our “Python for Absolute Beginners” courses - pt. 1 and 2.

column1: We expect you to be familiar with all the concepts described under "Python for Absolute Beginners" here:
https://kubdatalab.github.io/python
Pandas is a Python library specifically designed for working with structured data such as data organised in rows and columns
column2: similar to spreadsheets in Excel.

column1: Pandas is useful for students across all fields of study
column2: offering a toolkit for efficiently managing and analysing various types of structured data regardless of academic discipline.

column1: In this three-hour course
column2: you will develop an introductory understanding of Pandas. By the end of the course
column3: you will have gained insights into the following areas:

column1: <ul>
• Importing and exporting data with Pandas
• Creating new datasets and subsets by filtering data
• Using Pandas for analytical purposes
• Creating simple visualisations

4202471;R for Absolute Beginners;FALSE;2024-12-03T09:00:00Z;2024-12-03T11:00:00Z;"

R is a general programming language
column2: especially suited for statistical analysis and cleaning and visualization of data.

column1: We assume absolutely no previous experience with programming
column2: and will cover the basics of getting started with R

column1: <ul>
<li>Navigating in RStudio
column2: and how to interact with R

column1: <li>Datatypes
column2: variables and objects

column1: • Simple arithmetic and logical operations on data
• Working with functions - and how to write a very simple function ourself
• Import data into R
• Summary statistics
• Manipulating data frames
<li>And how to make a couple of the common graphs
column2: that are as useful as they are elementary.

column1: In preparation for the course
column2: we recommend that you either download and install R and RStudio
column3: or register for an account at rstudio.cloud. Instructions on this can be found here
column4: where you will also find the course notes
column5: additional material and exercises.

column1:
Please note that this course will be held in english if any participants requests it. Otherwise it will be held in danish.

4292401;Automatiseret transskription med værktøjet Whisper;FALSE;2024-12-03T12:15:00Z;2024-12-03T13:15:00Z;"

Workshoppen er en gennemgang af
column2: hvordan du kommer i gang med at anvende Whisper til at transskribere dine interviews. Efterfølgende kan du selv prøve kræfter med programmet
column3: og vi er der til at hjælpe dig i gang.

column1: Installationen af Whisper ligger på et Ucloud
column2: hvor der er adgang via WAYF
column3: og hvor dine data er i sikkerhed.

column1: Vi har en lydfil
column2: så du behøver ikke at medbringe dine egne data.

column1: Kursusmaterialet stammer fra AUL-BSS Datalab.

Læs mere om materialet på denne side.
